The Community Service Centre will now be operated at Eric Jiyane Hall opposite the Mhluzi police station. To access the station, the community can call the following number (013) 247 7000, for all emergencies and complainants which will be attended accordingly. The telephone lines at the Mhluzi police station Community Service Centre will not be accessible for the duration of the closure. However, service delivery will not be hampered. The building will be decontaminated tomorrow, Tuesday, 12 January 2021 and services will resume normally at the station on Wednesday, 13 January 2021. The SAPS management in Mpumalanga apologizes for any inconvenience that may arise from this. The Acting Station Commander, Captain David Mbenekazi can also be contacted on 082 065 1653.